{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1784439118,"nonce":"FvH3glJ1lT2mdvTvSPECnynH8+8=","message":"Phase 3 — PR 3 of the object series: PostgreSQL sequences. MERGED PR #113 (squash bd435a0). Epic stays OPEN.\n\nNew `SequenceModel { name, data_type, start, increment, min, max, cache, cycle, owned_by }` (+ SequenceDataType,\nSequenceOwnedBy) on `SchemaModel.sequences`, full object-template thread: IR → diff/plan → KDL → PG render +\nintrospection → MySQL/SQLite reject → SchemaCapabilities.sequences → CLI.\n\nScope decisions (maintainer, both \"full faithful\"):\n- Concrete attributes always rendered (AS type INCREMENT BY / MINVALUE / MAXVALUE / START WITH / CACHE / [NO ]CYCLE)\n  so a published sequence re-plans empty; a bare KDL sequence fills PG per-type defaults.\n- OWNED BY modeled + recovered from pg_depend. Diff splits ownership: bare CREATE SEQUENCE pre-table (a column\n  default could nextval it), ALTER SEQUENCE OWNED BY post-table (owner must exist); a sequence whose owner is\n  dropped is DETACHED first so PG doesn't cascade-drop it under the explicit DROP SEQUENCE.\n- Identity-column implicit sequences (pg_depend deptype 'i') EXCLUDED from introspection (created with the column);\n  serial / manual-OWNED-BY sequences (deptype 'a') surfaced with owner, matching pg_dump.\n\ncodex 6 rounds (all real, each disable-to-fail pinned): R1 detach-before-owner-drop + reject seq name collisions;\nR2 PAIR-SPECIFIC collision matrix — VERIFIED on PG17 that seq↔enum COLLIDE (a sequence owns an associated pg_type,\nso codex's \"they coexist\" premise was factually wrong while enum↔index do NOT; claim index/PK/unique backing-index\nnames; R3 SequenceModel invariant validation + KDL present-but-mistyped-attribute rejection (prop_i64/str/bool_checked)\n+ Alter{Index,PK,Unique} claims; R4 min\u003cmax STRICT (PG: MINVALUE","files":null}]}